==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Overhung
<hw>O"ver*hung"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Covered over; ornamented with hangings.</def>
<rj><au>Carlyle.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Suspended from above or from the top.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Overhung door</b></col>, <cd>a sliding door, suspended
door, suspended from the top, as upon rollers.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Overinfluence</ent>⟦br⟧
